pageContext.description: Containing rough piece of copper. Three ribs on each side
pageContext.other: Described under Site as "Founder's hoard. All found together by a workman in Nov 1880 near Meldreth Station Royston, Cambs. Stated to be the whole of the find." Under Associations described as 1-53 and listed as follows:,  17 socketed celts,  5 fragments ",  2  "     winged celts,  1 chisel,  1 gouge,  1 spearhead,  2 fragments  ",  6 fragments swords,  1 knife or razor,  2 pieces of edge of vessel,  1 rough piece from casting,  15 copper cakes,  9 odd fragments
pageContext.collection: British Museum,  80- 11- 24- 1,  Presented by AW Franks Esq,,  ( Henry Medland, Melbourn, Royston),  24/11/1880
